@NODE "DiskDoctor" "Part 58 - The DISKDOCTOR Command - Description"

@{B}@{U}The DISKDOCTOR Command@{UU} AmigaDOS Versions 2.0 and earlier@{UB}

The way to use this command is:-

  DISKDOCTOR drive

For example:-

  > DISKDOCTOR df1:

The command first reads all cylinders on the disk and makes its own internal
list of files that it finds.

When it finds directories or files that are recoverable you will be given
various messages such as:-

  REPLACING FILE filename
  REPLACING DIR dirname

If something is unreadable and/or unrecoverable, you will be told about
it and the file will be deleted.

Finally, you will receive a message:-

  Operation complete
  You should copy files required to a new disk and reformat this disk

Now you should copy all files to another formatted disk and try to reformat
the corrupt disk.

One time that it could be useful is if you have accidently given a disk
a "Quick" format (but NOT a full format!). DISKDOCTOR can recover all
the files on a disk that has been given a quick format.

It could also recover a file that has accidently been deleted PROVIDED
THAT NOTHING ELSE HAS BEEN WRITTEN TO THE DISK IN THE MEANTIME!!


