@NODE "Better" "Part 58 - The DISKDOCTOR Command - Better Ways"

@{B}@{U}Better Ways To Do The Job@{UB}@{UU}

There is an excellent SHAREWARE program called "DISKSALV2" by Dave Haynie
which does a far better job and a lot more things than DISKDOCTOR does. You
can find it in Aminet directory Disk/Salv. There is also a commercial
version DISKSALV3.

For my own disk salvage, I use the excellent commercial product
"AmiBackTools" which is a companion program to "AmiBack". If you have a
hard drive then you will find that programs such as "AmiBack" and
"AmiBackTools" are almost essential. If you already have a hard drive back
up program then check to see if it has disk salvage capabilities.

You will find that "DiskSalv" and "AmiBackTools" (and other equivalent
programs) will recover a lot more from a corrupt disk than "DiskDoctor"
will. Files with corrupt parts may not be fully recovered by "DiskSalv" or
"AmiBackTools" but, if they are text or data files, then it will be a great
help. Program files or files such as libraries that are only partly
recovered will not be of much use.

@{B}BUT@{UB} - read about the @{"BEST" LINK "Best"} way!


